01:27.000 --> 01:28.000
Why doesn't he come?

01:28.000 --> 01:30.000
It's been three weeks.

01:30.000 --> 01:31.969
Did he say he would?

01:33.000 --> 01:35.000
No...

01:35.000 --> 01:38.000
but he loves me, I am sure of it.

01:38.000 --> 01:40.000
Did he say so?

01:41.000 --> 01:45.000
Not in so many words. But how
could he look at me as he did

01:45.000 --> 01:47.000
and not mean it?

01:47.000 --> 01:48.619
And you?

01:50.000 --> 01:52.000
Do you love him?

01:53.000 --> 01:57.000
I do. I think I've loved him

01:57.000 --> 02:00.000
since the first time I
saw him at Otradnoe.

02:00.000 --> 02:03.000
It's not like it was with
Boris, or anyone. It's...

02:03.000 --> 02:07.000
It's so deep, it frightens me.

02:07.000 --> 02:09.000
So it must be true love, mustn't it?

02:09.000 --> 02:11.000
I suppose it must, my dear.

02:11.000 --> 02:14.686
Well then, why doesn't he come?

02:15.000 --> 02:18.000
I don't know, my darling.

02:18.000 --> 02:20.000
If it's meant to happen,
it will happen.

02:20.000 --> 02:22.000
There's nothing we can do about it.

02:22.000 --> 02:24.000
Go to bed, and see what
the morning will bring.

02:24.000 --> 02:26.000
- I can't, Mama.
- No more talk.

02:26.000 --> 02:28.000
Bed.

02:34.000 --> 02:37.000
Firstly, this marriage would
not be ideal in terms of family,

02:37.000 --> 02:38.000
wealth and distinction.

02:38.000 --> 02:40.000
The Rostovs are a perfectly
good family, Father.

02:40.000 --> 02:43.000
That may be, but you could do better
in that respect, and you know it.

02:43.000 --> 02:47.000
Secondly, you are not in early youth
and your health is not strong.

02:47.000 --> 02:51.000
You have never fully recovered from
the wound you took at Austerlitz.

02:52.000 --> 02:55.000
And you're in love
with this girl, you say.

02:55.000 --> 02:57.000
Very deeply, Father.

02:57.000 --> 02:58.000
Hah!

02:58.000 --> 03:02.553
Triumph of hope over
experience. All right.

03:04.000 --> 03:06.000
Will you do this for me?

03:06.000 --> 03:12.000
Take a year, go abroad, take a
cure, find a tutor for Nikolushka,

03:12.000 --> 03:15.000
and if, after this year,
your passion for this girl

03:15.000 --> 03:18.813
is still so irresistible,
marry her then.

03:20.000 --> 03:24.000
Can you do this? To please me?

03:46.000 --> 03:50.000
(HOOFBEATS)

03:53.000 --> 03:54.000
(SHE SIGHS)

03:54.000 --> 03:55.000
(HORSE WHINNIES)

04:09.000 --> 04:11.226
- Mama! Mama!
- Natasha.

04:11.383 --> 04:12.564
- It's him!
- What

04:12.564 --> 04:15.000
- It's him. What am I going to do?
- Prince Andrei Bolkonsky.

04:16.000 --> 04:21.000
Oh! Prince Andrei, it's a
pleasure to welcome you here.

04:21.000 --> 04:25.000
It seems so long
since we last saw you.

04:29.000 --> 04:33.000
Countess Rostova, may
I request your permission

04:33.000 --> 04:36.000
for a private conversation
with your daughter?

04:38.000 --> 04:40.000
Of course, Prince.

04:44.000 --> 04:46.000
Come with me.

05:02.000 --> 05:04.643
I loved you at the moment I saw you.

05:09.000 --> 05:11.000
May I hope...

05:14.000 --> 05:15.000
... you love me?

05:15.000 --> 05:18.587
Yes, yes! Yes, I love you.

05:33.000 --> 05:34.000
(SHE SOBS)

05:37.000 --> 05:40.000
I have to tell you that my father
made it a condition of his consent

05:40.000 --> 05:43.000
that the marriage not
take place for a year.

05:45.000 --> 05:47.000
I have some business to
conduct in Switzerland.

05:47.000 --> 05:49.000
Oh!

05:49.000 --> 05:51.000
It cannot be otherwise.

05:53.000 --> 05:56.000
I know a year seems like a long time,

05:56.000 --> 05:58.800
but it will give you the
chance to test your love.

06:00.000 --> 06:02.000
Our engagement will remain a secret.

06:04.000 --> 06:06.000
I consider myself bound,
but you should not.

06:07.000 --> 06:10.000
I want you to feel perfectly
free to change your mind.

06:13.000 --> 06:14.727
So long...

06:19.000 --> 06:21.000
No...

06:21.000 --> 06:22.638
I'll do it.

06:23.000 --> 06:25.000
I'll wait.

06:25.000 --> 06:27.000
(THEY CHUCKLE)

06:30.000 --> 06:32.000
(SHE LAUGHS)

06:42.000 --> 06:44.000
Thank you again.

06:44.000 --> 06:45.000
Goodbye.

06:54.000 --> 06:56.000
(SHE GASPS)

07:26.000 --> 07:29.000
(DOG PANTS)

07:29.000 --> 07:31.000
(HOUNDS BARK)

07:35.000 --> 07:37.000
(BARKING)

07:39.000 --> 07:42.000
(THUNDERING HOOVES)

07:45.000 --> 07:47.000
Come on, Rostov, keep up!

07:47.000 --> 07:49.000
Yah!

07:51.000 --> 07:52.000
(BARKING)

07:56.000 --> 07:57.000
(DOGS BARK AND WHINE)

07:57.000 --> 07:59.000
Dammit, lost him!

07:59.000 --> 08:01.000
(HORSES WHINNY)

08:01.000 --> 08:03.000
You, quick! Go around the side.

08:03.000 --> 08:04.000
Cut him off.

08:04.000 --> 08:07.000
Find him! Find the wolf!

08:07.000 --> 08:10.000
You heard him! Search over there!

08:10.000 --> 08:11.000
Come on!

08:11.000 --> 08:12.000
(HORSE WHINNIES)

08:17.000 --> 08:19.000
(BARKING AND SHOUTING IN DISTANCE)

08:22.000 --> 08:24.000
(SHE GASPS)

08:24.000 --> 08:26.000
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

08:29.000 --> 08:32.000
(WOLF PANTS)

08:34.000 --> 08:35.000
(SHE GASPS)

08:49.000 --> 08:51.000
(SHE GASPS)

08:51.000 --> 08:53.000
(BUGLE SOUNDS)

08:54.000 --> 08:56.000
(BARKING, HOOFBEATS)

08:56.000 --> 08:58.000
Cut them off!

08:58.000 --> 08:59.000
Quick! Cut them off!

09:01.000 --> 09:02.846
(MEN SING)

09:04.000 --> 09:06.000
You rode well.

09:06.000 --> 09:08.000
Thank you, I love to ride.

09:08.000 --> 09:11.000
- You weren't in at the finish, though.
- No.

09:13.000 --> 09:15.000
God, he was a big one.

09:15.000 --> 09:17.000
Yes, he was.

09:18.000 --> 09:19.633
I'm glad I didn't see the end.

09:21.000 --> 09:24.000
So, what's this engagement
all about, then?

09:24.000 --> 09:27.000
Well, I'm engaged, that's
all, and I'm very happy.

09:27.000 --> 09:29.000
He's a wonderful man, Nikki.

09:29.000 --> 09:31.000
Is he? I met him once.

09:31.000 --> 09:33.000
Seemed a bit of a cold fish to me.

09:33.000 --> 09:37.000
Oh, no, you're wrong,
he isn't! No, he's very...

09:39.000 --> 09:42.000
He's intense, and deep.
And he loves you?

09:42.000 --> 09:43.373
Yes, of course, he loves me!

09:43.374 --> 09:44.999
Well, then, why did he
go away for a year?

09:45.000 --> 09:46.000
Why not announce the betrothal?

09:46.000 --> 09:48.435
It's as if he's ashamed of our family!

09:48.435 --> 09:50.372
No. You don't understand,
and I don't want to talk about it

09:50.536 --> 09:52.000
- with you any more!
- Suit yourself.

09:52.000 --> 09:53.000
(HE CLICKS HORSE ON)

10:05.000 --> 10:07.000
Nikki, my dear,

10:07.000 --> 10:11.000
you must know that things
are very serious with our finances.

10:11.000 --> 10:13.000
As a woman, your sister has
no claim over Prince Andrei's estate

10:13.000 --> 10:17.000
and nothing your father tries
ever seems to work out,

10:17.000 --> 10:18.000
and he has such a generous nature

10:18.000 --> 10:21.000
that everybody takes
advantage of him.

10:23.000 --> 10:26.000
And you, my dear Nikki...

10:26.000 --> 10:30.000
with all that business about the
card game and your friend Dolokhov,

10:30.000 --> 10:32.000
that was a terrible blow
to the family fortunes.

10:32.000 --> 10:34.000
I know, Mama, and I'm sorry.

10:34.000 --> 10:39.000
I know you're sorry, and I know
you'll be very glad to hear

10:39.000 --> 10:42.000
that you have it in your power
to make all things well again.

10:43.000 --> 10:44.000
How can I do that?

10:49.000 --> 10:51.000
You remember Julie Karagina?

10:51.000 --> 10:54.000
- You used to be  playmates together.
- Er, yes...

10:54.000 --> 10:57.000
She has grown into a
lovely young woman.

10:57.000 --> 11:02.000
And now that her brothers
are all sadly... dead...

11:02.000 --> 11:06.000
she is an heiress
of a great fortune.

11:06.000 --> 11:09.000
Would you really demand
that I sacrifice my honour

11:09.000 --> 11:11.550
and my feelings for
the sake of money?

11:11.551 --> 11:12.999
No, no, of course not!

11:13.000 --> 11:17.627
You've misunderstood me. Of course,
we wish for your happiness.

11:18.000 --> 11:21.000
But you could be happy
with Julie Karagina,

11:21.000 --> 11:24.000
you could manage to
fall in love with her,

11:24.000 --> 11:26.000
there's nothing
wrong with her at all!

11:26.000 --> 11:29.000
Really, Mama, I can't
just command my feelings!

11:29.000 --> 11:34.000
I do understand, of course I do...
and I hate having to ask this...

11:34.000 --> 11:37.000
but our situation is desperate,

11:37.000 --> 11:41.474
and, as our son, you are
the only one who can help.

11:42.000 --> 11:44.000
I'll think about it, Mama.

11:46.000 --> 11:47.000
That's all I can say.

11:55.000 --> 11:58.000
These things have a way
of working out, my dear.

12:00.000 --> 12:04.000
Don't be cast down...
Christmas is coming!

12:04.000 --> 12:06.909
(SHE GROANS) More expense!

12:12.000 --> 12:15.000
This is what we need...
forget our troubles

12:15.000 --> 12:18.000
and get out to see
the real old Russia.

12:20.000 --> 12:23.000
Uncle Mikhail lives the way
we used to in the old days,

12:23.000 --> 12:25.000
- everyone together!
- Oh!

12:25.000 --> 12:27.000
Welcome, welcome!

12:27.000 --> 12:31.000
- Uncle Mikhail!
- We are honoured!

12:31.000 --> 12:35.000
- Hello!
- Countess Natasha, Cousin Sonya!

12:35.000 --> 12:36.000
There we are!

12:36.000 --> 12:39.000
Petya, how you've grown!

12:39.000 --> 12:43.000
Come on, come on, out
of the cold, come inside!

12:43.000 --> 12:46.000
- Sit, sit, make yourselves comfortable!
- Thank you!

12:46.000 --> 12:48.634
Anisya, our guests are here!

12:49.000 --> 12:52.000
Don't worry, we saw you coming.

12:52.000 --> 12:54.000
- Look at this!
- Lovely!

12:54.000 --> 12:57.000
You are welcome...
please, sit, eat, drink...

12:57.000 --> 12:59.000
- Oh, delicious!
- What a spread!

12:59.000 --> 13:01.000
I'm so happy you're here.

13:01.000 --> 13:03.000
(MIKHAIL CHUCKLES)

13:03.000 --> 13:06.381
- I didn't know Uncle was married!
- Well, he isn't.

13:08.000 --> 13:10.000
(QUIET CHATTER)

13:12.000 --> 13:15.000
(SHE SINGS IN RUSSIAN)

13:20.000 --> 13:22.000
(HUSHED CHATTER)

13:25.000 --> 13:27.000
(ALL CHATTER)

13:36.000 --> 13:40.000
(ALL BEGIN TO SING)

13:47.000 --> 13:50.000
(ALL SING)

14:00.000 --> 14:04.000
(ALL SING LOUDLY)

14:07.000 --> 14:10.000
(ALL CLAP IN TIME)

14:44.000 --> 14:47.594
- How does she know what to do?
- It's in the blood.

15:08.000 --> 15:10.000
(SHE YELLS)

15:10.000 --> 15:12.000
(MUSIC GETS FASTER)

15:16.000 --> 15:18.000
(ALL CHEER)

15:18.000 --> 15:21.000
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

15:26.000 --> 15:27.000
(SHE PANTS)

15:29.000 --> 15:34.000
He looked just like an ordinary man,
like an officer, but it was him!

15:34.000 --> 15:37.000
Now, what she should have
done was keep him talking,

15:37.000 --> 15:41.000
but she got so frightened
and she tried to run away,

15:41.000 --> 15:43.000
and he grabbed her!

15:43.000 --> 15:45.000
(THEY GASP)

15:49.000 --> 15:52.000
You don't need to worry
about him here now.

15:52.000 --> 15:53.678
But you can tell your fortune..

15:54.000 --> 15:56.500
... if you go out to
the barn at night.

15:56.501 --> 15:57.835
How? What do you do?

15:58.000 --> 16:00.000
You stand and you listen...

16:00.000 --> 16:03.000
and if you hear
knocking, that's bad,

16:03.000 --> 16:06.000
but if you hear grain pouring,

16:06.000 --> 16:07.000
it's good.

16:07.000 --> 16:11.552
But I don't suppose any of
you would go out there.

16:12.000 --> 16:14.000
I would.

16:14.000 --> 16:16.000
I'm not scared.

16:19.000 --> 16:20.000
Show me the way?

16:20.000 --> 16:22.647
Yes, miss. Follow me.

16:30.000 --> 16:32.000
That's the barn there, miss.

16:32.000 --> 16:34.569
Don't look back.

17:07.000 --> 17:08.000
(DOOR CREAKS)

17:10.000 --> 17:12.000
(SHE GASPS)

17:16.000 --> 17:17.560
Sonya.

17:19.000 --> 17:20.000
Nikolai.

17:46.000 --> 17:47.000
Are you cold?

17:48.000 --> 17:49.000
Not a bit.

17:51.000 --> 17:52.000
Tasha?

17:53.000 --> 17:55.964
No, I'm perfect.

17:57.000 --> 18:00.000
We could live like this,
in the country, all the time.

18:00.000 --> 18:02.000
I wish!

18:03.000 --> 18:05.000
Do you? Do you really?

18:09.000 --> 18:11.000
Of course, I love
Andrei. Of course, I do.

18:11.000 --> 18:14.000
And I miss him and I long for him,

18:14.000 --> 18:16.626
- but at the same time...
- Look! The comet!

18:18.000 --> 18:21.796
You know, people say it means
a great change is coming.

18:22.000 --> 18:25.000
I sometimes wish nothing
would ever change...

18:26.000 --> 18:30.000
... it could be just you and
me and Sonya, like this.

18:30.000 --> 18:31.000
Stay like children.

18:32.000 --> 18:33.000
Not possible.

18:34.000 --> 18:36.000
Tonight, it is.

18:48.000 --> 18:49.000
Mother, Father...

18:50.000 --> 18:55.000
I have something I want to say to
you before I return to my regiment.

18:55.000 --> 18:57.000
- (TEACUPS CLATTER)
- I must tell you...

18:58.000 --> 19:00.000
... that I am in love with Sonya...

19:01.000 --> 19:03.000
... and I want us to be married.

19:04.000 --> 19:08.000
I know it's not what you want for
me, but my feelings can't be denied

19:08.000 --> 19:10.000
and I want Sonya to hear this, too.

19:10.000 --> 19:12.000
I love her.

19:13.000 --> 19:16.585
I've never loved anyone else,
I could never marry anyone else.

19:18.000 --> 19:20.000
And that's all there
is to it. I'm sorry.

19:20.000 --> 19:23.000
Nevertheless, you go
against your parents' wishes.

19:23.000 --> 19:26.347
Well, you are of age, Nikolai,

19:26.571 --> 19:27.999
so you can marry anyone you choose,

19:28.000 --> 19:30.000
but neither I nor your father
will give you our blessing!

19:30.000 --> 19:32.468
Please, don't let us
quarrel over this, Mama...

19:32.469 --> 19:33.736
Ilya! Speak to him.

19:34.000 --> 19:37.000
My dear boy, if it weren't
for the circumstances,

19:37.000 --> 19:39.000
we couldn't wish for a
better match than Sonya.

19:39.000 --> 19:42.482
She's a dear girl and
we're very fond of her...

19:42.483 --> 19:44.999
- What circumstances?
- You know the circumstances very well!

19:45.000 --> 19:48.000
Our family affairs are in disorder

19:48.000 --> 19:51.000
and we've been expecting
you to help put them right!

19:51.000 --> 19:55.000
Your conduct so far has had the
opposite effect, as you well know.

19:55.000 --> 19:57.000
Besides, Sonya is your cousin.

19:57.000 --> 20:00.000
How you could have let
her wheedle her way...

20:00.000 --> 20:02.000
My feelings are my own, Mother,

20:02.000 --> 20:04.000
and I can't go back on my word.

20:04.000 --> 20:07.000
Then you'd better know
that I can never recognise

20:07.000 --> 20:10.000
that intriguer as my
daughter! "Intriguer"?!

20:11.000 --> 20:12.000
How can you use such a word

20:12.000 --> 20:15.000
about a girl who's always
loved you like a daughter?!

20:15.000 --> 20:17.000
Sonya is not to blame
for this in any way!

20:17.000 --> 20:19.000
Have you no feelings for her at all?

20:19.000 --> 20:21.000
I have nothing else to say to you!

20:21.000 --> 20:22.000
Mama, I...

20:25.000 --> 20:27.000
(SONYA SOBS)

20:27.000 --> 20:28.700
Perhaps I should go after her.

20:28.701 --> 20:31.000
No, no, let me...
I can explain to her.

20:31.000 --> 20:34.000
It will be all right,
I...I...I know it will.

20:34.000 --> 20:36.000
(FOOTSTEPS RETREAT)

20:41.000 --> 20:42.000
'That ungrateful girl!'

20:42.000 --> 20:45.000
After everything we've
done for her! (SHE SNIFFLES)

20:45.000 --> 20:47.000
She's not ungrateful, Mama,
you know that, really.

20:47.000 --> 20:49.000
None of this is her fault,

20:49.000 --> 20:52.000
she didn't know that Nikolai
was going to speak out.

20:52.000 --> 20:55.000
Truly, she's never expected
anything from him.

20:55.000 --> 20:57.000
And now, my son hates me! (SHE SOBS)

20:57.000 --> 20:59.000
He doesn't!

20:59.000 --> 21:01.000
Oh, he doesn't!

21:01.000 --> 21:03.000
He wants your blessing.

21:05.000 --> 21:09.000
Listen, if I can get him to promise
he won't do anything in secret.

21:09.000 --> 21:11.000
He'll go back to his regiment,
and who knows,

21:11.000 --> 21:14.000
- perhaps his feelings will cool down.
- Oh, now you know so much of love.

21:14.000 --> 21:17.000
(SHE SOBS AND GASPS)

21:17.000 --> 21:20.000
Don't let him go with any
bad feeling between you.

21:20.000 --> 21:22.000
Because who knows what may happen.

21:22.000 --> 21:26.086
Nothing I ever think, or do, or say

21:26.261 --> 21:27.999
ever seems to make any difference.

21:28.000 --> 21:29.803
Our family is in ruin!

21:31.000 --> 21:33.000
I'm the only one who cares.

21:33.000 --> 21:35.000
(SHE SIGHS)

21:35.000 --> 21:37.000
Oh, Mama.

21:38.000 --> 21:40.000
(THEY SIGH)

21:42.000 --> 21:43.000
Take care, Petya.

21:49.000 --> 21:51.625
- I love you!
- I love you, too.

22:11.000 --> 22:12.000
Look after yourself.

22:12.000 --> 22:14.000
I will, Papa, I will.

22:14.000 --> 22:16.000
(THEY SNIFF)

22:36.000 --> 22:38.000
Yah! Yah!

23:01.000 --> 23:05.000
PRINCE BOLKONSKY: That's it!
That's it! Make haste!

23:05.000 --> 23:07.138
- Is this our house, too?
- Mm-hm,

23:07.163 --> 23:08.999
this is our Moscow house.

23:09.000 --> 23:11.000
It smells funny.

23:11.000 --> 23:14.000
It just needs airing,
darling, that's all.

23:14.000 --> 23:18.105
I expect your grandpapa will be
redecorating it in cheerful colours.

23:18.230 --> 23:19.999
He certainly will not!
It's perfectly fine as it is.

23:20.000 --> 23:21.000
We will dine at six.

23:21.000 --> 23:24.076
I am going to my study and will
not to be disturbed until then.

23:24.215 --> 23:26.999
I have much work to do,
important political work of the kind

23:27.000 --> 23:30.357
that women and children
CANNOT BEGIN TO UNDERSTAND!

23:34.000 --> 23:37.000
Forgive me, Mademoiselle Bourienne.

23:37.000 --> 23:39.000
Oh, dear Prince,
I quite understand...

23:39.000 --> 23:41.000
Do you? Do you?

23:41.000 --> 23:43.000
Oh, you dear little thing!

23:43.000 --> 23:46.000
When I talk of the stupidity of women,

23:46.000 --> 23:48.602
I refer to THAT one, not you.

23:57.000 --> 23:58.000
Really!

23:58.000 --> 24:00.000
What?

24:00.000 --> 24:03.000
How can you take advantage
of his weakness like that?

24:03.000 --> 24:05.000
You play up to him!

24:05.000 --> 24:08.000
You make a fool of him
and yourself and me!

24:08.000 --> 24:11.000
(RETREATING FOOTSTEPS)

24:19.000 --> 24:23.000
Do you think Prince Andrei will be
in Moscow by the time we get there?

24:23.000 --> 24:25.000
Has he said anything definite?

24:25.000 --> 24:27.000
No, not absolutely definite.

24:28.000 --> 24:30.609
Don't get your hopes up too high.

24:32.000 --> 24:33.000
He'll come when he comes.

24:49.000 --> 24:51.000
Oh!

24:51.000 --> 24:52.609
What is it, my love?

24:54.000 --> 24:57.000
- Andrei's not coming after all!
- Oh! (COUNT ROSTOV SIGHS)

24:57.000 --> 24:58.000
He says his wound has reopened,

24:58.000 --> 25:03.000
and his doctors have insisted
he have rest and treatment for it.

25:03.000 --> 25:05.000
He sends his respects to you,

25:05.000 --> 25:09.000
and his... his love to me,
and his disappointment, et cetera.

25:09.000 --> 25:11.000
(SHE SOBS)

25:11.000 --> 25:14.000
But why couldn't he come
and have his treatment for it here?

25:14.000 --> 25:17.000
He has to respect
his doctors' advice, my dear.

25:17.000 --> 25:20.000
A long journey might have
a very bad effect on his health.

25:20.000 --> 25:22.000
Take heart,

25:22.000 --> 25:25.000
I'm sure you'll see
him before too long.

25:25.000 --> 25:26.000
But I want to see him now!

25:27.000 --> 25:30.000
Before long I'll have forgotten
what he looks like!

25:30.000 --> 25:31.000
(RETREATING FOOTSTEPS)

25:31.000 --> 25:33.000
(SHE SIGHS)

25:33.000 --> 25:36.000
(CHATTERING)

25:36.000 --> 25:37.000
That's the daughter.

25:37.000 --> 25:40.000
Oh, so, that's why
we're here. Not a beauty.

25:40.000 --> 25:44.000
But a prize, Boris. A
prize. Best behaviour.

25:44.000 --> 25:45.000
Prince Bolkonsky. Madam.

25:45.000 --> 25:47.000
- Prince Bolkonsky.
- Madam.

25:47.000 --> 25:50.000
An honour to be invited on your
name day... many felicitations...

25:50.000 --> 25:52.000
may I present my son, Boris?

25:52.000 --> 25:53.000
Honoured, Your Excellency.

25:53.000 --> 25:56.000
Yes, well, you're very welcome.

25:56.000 --> 25:58.000
Ah, Rostopchin!

26:00.000 --> 26:03.000
It's Count Rostopchin, Mother!
He's the Governor of Moscow!

26:03.000 --> 26:05.000
Talk to the Princess!

26:05.000 --> 26:06.916
(HE SIGHS)

26:09.000 --> 26:10.638
Princess Marya.

26:13.000 --> 26:15.000
Boris Drubetskoy.

26:16.000 --> 26:18.000
Such a pleasure to meet you at last.

26:18.000 --> 26:20.000
May I ask,

26:20.000 --> 26:22.000
how are you enjoying Moscow?

26:22.000 --> 26:24.618
I have seen very little of it, sir.

26:25.000 --> 26:28.576
Then perhaps you will allow me to
show you some of its finer points?

26:33.000 --> 26:35.000
I believe you know
my friend Bezukhov?

26:43.000 --> 26:47.000
Bonaparte behaves in Europe
like a pirate on a captured ship.

26:47.000 --> 26:49.000
And his ambition knows no bounds!

26:49.000 --> 26:51.000
It'll come to war again,
mark my words! No, no, Prince.

26:51.000 --> 26:54.000
Our Tsar has the wisdom and
courage to hold him in check.

26:54.000 --> 26:55.000
But I tell you this...

26:55.000 --> 26:59.000
our wars with the French
will be unsuccessful

26:59.000 --> 27:02.000
as long as we meddle in Europe.

27:02.000 --> 27:05.000
Let us keep our borders
safe and strong,

27:05.000 --> 27:07.000
and then we have no need
to fear Bonaparte.

27:07.000 --> 27:10.000
Let him venture into Russia,
and we'll send him home...

27:10.000 --> 27:12.000
squealing, with his tail
between his legs! Eh?!

27:12.000 --> 27:15.000
- (THUMPING ON TABLE)
- Well said, Prince! Well said!

27:15.000 --> 27:17.000
(ANIMATED MURMURS)

27:18.000 --> 27:20.000
May I sit with you?

27:20.000 --> 27:23.439
Oh, yes. I was hoping you would.

27:25.000 --> 27:26.000
(HE SIGHS)

27:26.000 --> 27:28.000
So, how did you like the young man?

27:28.000 --> 27:30.000
Who?

27:30.000 --> 27:32.000
Boris Drubetskoy.

27:32.000 --> 27:35.000
He was making himself
very agreeable to you.

27:35.000 --> 27:37.000
Oh!

27:37.000 --> 27:38.693
Yes. I suppose he was.

27:39.000 --> 27:41.000
Would you consider marrying him?

27:43.000 --> 27:46.667
Well, I sometimes think I'd
marry anyone to get away...

27:50.000 --> 27:52.000
I don't think he means to be cruel.

27:52.000 --> 27:54.000
I know, I know, forget what I said.

27:54.000 --> 27:56.000
(SHE SWALLOWS A SOB)

27:56.000 --> 27:58.000
Will you tell me truly, Count,

27:58.000 --> 28:01.000
what's she like,
this Natasha Rostova?

28:01.000 --> 28:03.000
It's only...

28:03.000 --> 28:07.742
Andrei is risking so much
in opposing our father.

28:08.000 --> 28:10.000
Is she really worth it?

28:11.000 --> 28:13.000
How can I answer
a question like that?

28:16.000 --> 28:18.000
For myself...

28:18.000 --> 28:21.000
I would say, there's no-one like her.

28:22.000 --> 28:24.000
She's enchanting.

28:24.000 --> 28:25.000
I... I don't know.

28:26.000 --> 28:29.000
But to me, yes,
she'd be worth anything.

28:29.000 --> 28:31.000
Everything.

28:32.000 --> 28:34.000
(SHE CHUCKLES)

28:37.000 --> 28:41.000
Honestly, Mother, I tried my
best, but it was hopeless.

28:41.000 --> 28:44.000
She hardly seemed
to notice I was there.

28:44.000 --> 28:46.000
There's something clearly
wrong with her.

28:46.000 --> 28:48.000
Perhaps she's mentally deficient.

28:49.000 --> 28:51.000
There's always Julie Karagina.

28:51.000 --> 28:54.000
She likes me, and she's quite
as rich as the other one.

28:54.000 --> 28:57.690
- She has other suitors, Boris.
- I know how to handle her.

28:58.000 --> 29:01.000
She likes romantic poetry,
anything melancholy,

29:01.000 --> 29:03.000
weeping willows and so on.

29:03.000 --> 29:05.612
Plenty of sighing, you know?

29:06.000 --> 29:10.000
She imagines she's had
a tragic life.

29:10.000 --> 29:11.000
God knows why...

29:11.000 --> 29:12.930
Well, there you are, then.

29:14.000 --> 29:16.619
The thing is, could I bear
to be married to her?

29:22.000 --> 29:23.682
(HE SIGHS)

29:25.000 --> 29:26.954
What a sad face.

29:28.000 --> 29:30.000
I can tell that you have suffered...

29:30.000 --> 29:31.000
as I have.

29:33.000 --> 29:34.000
Yes.

29:34.000 --> 29:36.000
You and I, Julie,

29:36.000 --> 29:39.787
sometimes I think we are both too
sensitive for this cruel world.

29:39.788 --> 29:42.779
- Yes.
- The blind, uncaring masses...

29:45.000 --> 29:47.000
But you're actually getting on
quite well, aren't you?

29:47.000 --> 29:53.000
Ah, Julie, I play their
games because I have to.

29:53.000 --> 29:54.565
But in my heart...

29:59.000 --> 30:00.000
I...

30:00.000 --> 30:03.000
I so love the drawing and the verse

30:03.000 --> 30:05.000
you put in my album, Boris.

30:10.000 --> 30:14.577
"Ah, rustic trees, your
shade conceals my sorrow...

30:15.000 --> 30:20.000
"Ah, cloudy sky,
will I find light tomorrow?"

30:21.000 --> 30:23.000
Do you know, I believe you will!

30:27.000 --> 30:30.000
Is your son not with you? Boris?

30:30.000 --> 30:33.000
No, he spends all his time at
Julie Karagina's these days.

30:33.000 --> 30:35.000
Of course, you haven't heard!

30:35.000 --> 30:38.000
He's the accepted suitor,
they're going to be married!

30:38.000 --> 30:42.000
Oh! What... wonderful news!

30:42.000 --> 30:44.000
Your former admirer, Natasha.

30:44.000 --> 30:47.000
Don't tease me, Papa,
we were just children, then.

30:48.000 --> 30:50.000
I'm very happy for Boris,
Anna Mikhailovna.

30:50.000 --> 30:54.000
Yes, he's done very well for
himself, but who deserves it better?

30:54.000 --> 30:56.000
He was always such a good boy.

30:56.000 --> 30:57.000
- (LAUGHING)
- He was!

30:57.000 --> 30:59.698
And your fiance is coming soon?

31:02.000 --> 31:04.000
Yes... Yes, that is...

31:04.000 --> 31:08.000
Such a long time to be
separated, you must feel it.

31:08.000 --> 31:11.000
But his father, you know,
he's a very difficult old man,

31:11.000 --> 31:16.000
and getting worse by the day...
we dined there a little while ago...

31:17.000 --> 31:20.000
- Very strong opinions!
- Oh, dear...

31:20.000 --> 31:23.000
Oh, but the little
Princess Marya's very, um...

31:23.000 --> 31:25.000
soft and sweet.

31:25.000 --> 31:27.000
A sister-in-law can be a sharp claw,

31:27.000 --> 31:29.000
but this one wouldn't hurt a fly.

31:29.000 --> 31:32.000
If I were you, I'd go and call
on them tomorrow with your father.

31:32.000 --> 31:34.550
What do you think, Papa?

31:36.000 --> 31:38.000
I suppose we should, yes...

31:38.000 --> 31:40.000
I'm a little frightened of the Prince.

31:40.000 --> 31:42.000
He gave me a terrible
roasting not so long ago

31:42.000 --> 31:44.000
over my failings with the militia.

31:44.000 --> 31:47.000
- (WOMEN LAUGH)
- I'm sure all that's forgotten, Ilya!

31:47.000 --> 31:49.000
I think Anna's idea is a good one.

31:49.000 --> 31:51.000
When Prince Andrei returns,

31:51.000 --> 31:53.000
you'll be already acquainted
with his sister and his father.

31:53.000 --> 31:57.000
- I suppose so.
- Well, that's settled, then.

32:04.000 --> 32:05.000
Now, then.

32:05.000 --> 32:07.000
(DOOR BELL RINGS)

32:16.000 --> 32:18.000
Would you be so good
as to wait here, sir?

32:20.000 --> 32:21.000
Hm...

32:28.000 --> 32:30.000
(STAFF WHISPER INDISTINCTLY)

32:30.000 --> 32:32.000
- Well, bless my soul, this is odd.
- (DOOR SLAMS)

32:32.000 --> 32:34.000
Is someone ill, I wonder?

32:35.000 --> 32:37.000
BOLKONSKY, FROM INSIDE: What?!
I don't want them in my house!

32:37.000 --> 32:39.274
I never asked for them!
You can see them if you like!

32:39.275 --> 32:40.498
Papa!

32:41.000 --> 32:43.000
- (NATASHA GASPS)
- Perhaps we should go...

32:43.000 --> 32:46.000
My dear Count Rostov, I'm so sorry
you have been kept waiting.

32:46.000 --> 32:51.000
The Prince is indisposed,
but Princess Marya will receive you.

32:51.000 --> 32:53.000
I am her companion.

32:53.000 --> 32:54.859
Please, come this way.

33:09.000 --> 33:12.000
Dear Princess, you see,
I brought my little...

33:12.000 --> 33:14.000
singing bird.

33:14.000 --> 33:16.712
I'm so sorry my father
can't receive you.

33:16.864 --> 33:17.999
Well, another time.

33:18.000 --> 33:21.564
But for now, it gives the two
of you the chance to get acquainted.

33:24.000 --> 33:27.000
How do you like Moscow,
Countess Rostova?

33:27.000 --> 33:30.000
Well enough, thank you.
I grew up here, it's my home.

33:30.000 --> 33:31.000
Oh, but of course!

33:31.000 --> 33:34.000
It is we who are the country mice.

33:34.000 --> 33:38.000
And I must say, I love the shops
and the theatre so very much.

33:41.000 --> 33:43.000
But the Princess is not such a one

33:43.000 --> 33:46.000
for the pleasures of
the city, are you?

33:47.000 --> 33:48.657
No.

33:50.000 --> 33:54.000
How delightful this is! You two must
have so much to say to each other!

33:58.000 --> 33:59.000
Um...

33:59.000 --> 34:03.000
Perhaps, mademoiselle,
we should leave them together?

34:03.000 --> 34:05.000
(DOOR OPENS)

34:05.000 --> 34:07.000
Ah! Rostov! I didn't know!

34:07.000 --> 34:10.000
As God's my witness, I didn't know!

34:11.000 --> 34:13.000
And this is the young countess?

34:15.000 --> 34:16.000
Uh...

34:17.000 --> 34:19.000
Uh...

34:19.000 --> 34:21.000
Well, you see, I know nothing
of this, you must forgive me.

34:21.000 --> 34:24.000
As God's my witness, I didn't know!

34:24.000 --> 34:27.000
And no-one said
anything to me ABOUT IT!

34:28.000 --> 34:30.000
Good morning.

34:33.000 --> 34:35.000
(DOOR SLAMS)

34:35.000 --> 34:37.000
Natasha, I think we should be
going. We've come at a bad time.

34:37.000 --> 34:40.000
You must come to us
for the day, Princess.

34:40.000 --> 34:43.000
A pleasure to meet you,
mademoiselle.

34:43.000 --> 34:45.000
Oh, wait!

34:46.000 --> 34:48.000
Dearest Natasha...

34:48.000 --> 34:50.000
Please know that I'm...

34:52.000 --> 34:54.000
... glad my brother
has found happiness...

34:54.000 --> 34:57.000
I think perhaps this is not the
time to speak of it, Princess.

34:57.000 --> 34:59.000
Goodbye.

35:02.000 --> 35:03.000
(DOOR SLAMS)

35:06.000 --> 35:08.160
NATASHA: 'Oh, it was horrible!'

35:09.000 --> 35:11.000
I was horrible to her! (SHE SOBS)

35:11.000 --> 35:14.906
But she was so cold and stiff
with me! And the old prince...

35:15.000 --> 35:18.000
(SHE SOBS) They don't like me.

35:18.000 --> 35:21.000
They don't want me in their family.

35:21.000 --> 35:22.000
(SHE WEEPS)

35:25.000 --> 35:27.000
Oh, if only Andrei would come!

35:27.000 --> 35:29.000
(SHE CRIES)

35:35.000 --> 35:37.000
- Three and a six...
- (DICE ROLLS)

35:40.000 --> 35:41.684
Good afternoon, Count!

35:43.000 --> 35:45.635
Good afternoon.

35:46.000 --> 35:48.000
Boris was just telling me
he's very keen

35:48.000 --> 35:51.000
to be initiated into the
mysteries of the Freemasons.

35:51.000 --> 35:52.473
You could arrange that for

35:52.498 --> 35:53.999
- him, couldn't you?
- Really?

35:54.000 --> 35:57.000
- You're truly interested?
- Of course I am.

35:58.000 --> 36:00.000
It would be so good for his
career, wouldn't it, Pierre?

36:00.000 --> 36:02.000
That is not the true
purpose of the Order!

36:02.000 --> 36:05.000
To become a Mason, you
have to vow to purify yourself

36:05.000 --> 36:08.000
and dedicate yourself
to building a better world...

36:08.000 --> 36:09.999
you have to live for your fellow man.

36:10.000 --> 36:14.000
Yes, that, too,
of course! Absolutely!

36:14.000 --> 36:15.000
You'll help him, won't you, Pierre?

36:15.000 --> 36:17.000
Pierre's awfully high up
in the Masons...

36:17.000 --> 36:18.040
I think he might be Grand

36:18.065 --> 36:19.000
- Master by now!
- Helene!

36:19.361 --> 36:20.334
These things are not
to be spoken of

36:20.335 --> 36:23.000
- outside the house.
- I keep forgetting!

36:23.000 --> 36:25.000
You will help him, won't you?

36:28.000 --> 36:31.000
You are truly serious?

36:31.000 --> 36:34.800
As serious as any man
can be, Count Bezukhov.

36:48.000 --> 36:51.000
BAZDEEV: 'What have you done
with all these good things

36:51.000 --> 36:53.000
'that have been given you?

36:56.000 --> 36:58.000
'You need to purify yourself.

37:00.000 --> 37:01.671
'Listen to your conscience.

37:03.000 --> 37:05.000
'Look at yourself.'

37:05.000 --> 37:09.000
ALL: Sic transit gloria mundi!

37:09.000 --> 37:11.000
'Ask yourself...'

37:11.000 --> 37:13.000
(THEY MOAN)

37:14.000 --> 37:16.708
'... are you content with yourself?

37:19.000 --> 37:20.000
'With your life?'

37:20.000 --> 37:22.000
(HE COUGHS)

37:27.000 --> 37:29.000
We just won't go, Natalya.

37:29.000 --> 37:30.000
Nonsense!

37:30.000 --> 37:32.000
It's only a little turn.

37:32.000 --> 37:35.000
Go to the opera, enjoy
yourself, my dear!

37:35.000 --> 37:37.000
And you can tell me all about it.

37:37.000 --> 37:38.477
It'll take your mind off things,

37:38.502 --> 37:39.999
- you'll see.
- I don't want to go.

37:40.000 --> 37:42.000
I don't want to see anybody.

37:42.000 --> 37:44.000
Let me stay and keep you company.

37:44.000 --> 37:47.000
I don't need company. I just
need a little rest, that's all.

37:48.000 --> 37:50.000
Come and kiss me.

37:54.000 --> 37:55.000
There.

37:55.000 --> 37:57.000
Now, go.

37:58.000 --> 37:59.000
GO!

38:18.000 --> 38:20.869
... next time you'll have
to be better...

38:29.000 --> 38:31.000
I'm not nagging, but I
do think it would be nice

38:31.000 --> 38:32.000
if you tried a little harder...

38:32.000 --> 38:35.000
Just popped in to say
what a pleasure it is

38:35.000 --> 38:37.000
to see you back in
Moscow, Count Rostov.

38:37.000 --> 38:39.000
Very good of you, dear boy.

38:39.000 --> 38:42.000
I say! Look there!
Isn't that young Dolokhov?

38:42.000 --> 38:44.000
And why is he dressed
like a Persian?

38:44.000 --> 38:46.000
Ah, yes, he was in the Caucasus,

38:46.000 --> 38:48.000
and then he became minister
to some prince in Persia,

38:48.000 --> 38:50.000
and killed the Shah's brother there.

38:52.000 --> 38:55.829
That's Anatole Kuragin,
the Countess's brother.

38:56.000 --> 38:58.572
Very attractive, no?

38:59.000 --> 39:02.000
Ah, here's the Countess herself.

39:04.000 --> 39:06.000
Fine woman, isn't she?

39:06.000 --> 39:08.712
She's as beautiful as everybody says.

39:13.000 --> 39:15.000
(HUSH DESCENDS)

39:17.000 --> 39:22.000
(SHE SINGS ARIA)

39:38.000 --> 39:42.000
Count Rostov, you must introduce
me to your lovely daughters.

39:42.000 --> 39:45.000
Of course. Here's Natasha,

39:45.000 --> 39:47.000
and this is my niece, Sonya.

39:47.000 --> 39:49.000
I'm so happy to meet you.

39:50.000 --> 39:54.000
My husband has talked of you often.
I should so like to know you better.

39:54.000 --> 39:56.000
Count, may I invite your
daughter to sit with us?

39:56.000 --> 39:58.000
I'm sure she'd be delighted.

39:58.000 --> 40:01.552
Go on, Natasha, we shan't be far away.

40:08.000 --> 40:10.554
Come and sit by me.

40:11.000 --> 40:14.000
Not you, Bilibin, off you go.

40:14.000 --> 40:17.000
- Merci, bien.
- De rien.

40:19.000 --> 40:21.000
That's such a pretty dress.

40:21.000 --> 40:23.650
I wish I could still
wear something like that.

40:25.000 --> 40:27.000
You know I have no-one
to talk about clothes...

40:27.000 --> 40:30.000
- would you come and advise me?
- Advise you?

40:31.000 --> 40:34.000
I wouldn't dare! Well, you can come
and tell me what you like then.

40:34.000 --> 40:37.000
We can try things on together,
would you like that?

40:37.000 --> 40:39.000
Yes, very much.

40:39.000 --> 40:40.000
Then we'll be friends.

40:41.000 --> 40:44.000
Now that I've found you
I won't let you go.

40:44.000 --> 40:46.000
(NATASHA CHUCKLES)

40:51.000 --> 40:53.468
Ah! My brother Anatole.

40:59.000 --> 41:00.000
Well...

41:01.000 --> 41:03.000
... here we are.

41:04.000 --> 41:06.000
This is very nice, isn't it?

41:06.000 --> 41:08.619
Yes, it is...

41:10.000 --> 41:13.000
- You mean the opera?
- Not just the opera.

41:14.000 --> 41:15.524
You know...

41:16.000 --> 41:18.000
... all of it.

41:22.000 --> 41:23.000
Yes.

41:27.000 --> 41:28.499
You're so lovely.

41:30.000 --> 41:33.000
- You mustn't say that!
- Whyever not?

41:33.000 --> 41:34.000
It's the truth.

41:34.000 --> 41:37.000
And I was brought up
to tell the truth at all times.

41:37.000 --> 41:39.000
(OPERA SINGING FADES)

41:39.000 --> 41:43.000
Listen, we're having a little
party tomorrow evening.

41:43.000 --> 41:45.000
Just a few friends.

41:48.000 --> 41:50.576
Please, do come.

41:53.000 --> 41:55.000
Vous serez la plus jolie.

41:56.000 --> 41:59.000
Venez, et comme gage
donnez-moi cette fleur.

42:06.000 --> 42:07.000
(HE CHUCKLES)

42:07.000 --> 42:09.000
(SHE GASPS)

42:13.000 --> 42:14.000
(SHE BREATHES RAGGEDLY)

42:22.000 --> 42:23.000
(SHE GASPS)

42:35.000 --> 42:40.000
(MUSIC DROWNS CONVERSATION)

43:04.000 --> 43:07.000
Oh! No, no, no,
Countess! Keep still.

43:07.000 --> 43:10.000
Everything must be perfect
for when the Prince returns!

43:12.000 --> 43:13.000
I'll only be a minute.

43:13.000 --> 43:15.000
Yes, miss.

43:15.000 --> 43:18.000
They said you weren't decent,
but I told them you wouldn't mind...

43:18.000 --> 43:19.450
- and you don't, do you?
- No.

43:20.000 --> 43:22.000
You look adorable.

43:22.000 --> 43:26.000
Well, the word has gone round,
you've conquered Moscow already.

43:26.000 --> 43:28.969
It's quite funny, my brother
came for breakfast this morning,

43:29.103 --> 43:32.000
but he couldn't eat a thing.
Can you guess why?

43:32.000 --> 43:33.700
No, why?

43:35.000 --> 43:38.000
Oh, look at you blushing!

43:38.000 --> 43:41.000
I'm sure you know very well the
effect you've had on the poor boy.

43:41.000 --> 43:44.000
Anyway, you're to come
to us this evening.

43:44.000 --> 43:47.000
Just a little party. Mademoiselle
George will be there...

43:47.000 --> 43:50.000
she's promised us a recitation,
and she's dying to meet you.

43:50.000 --> 43:53.000
I've already asked
your papa's permission.

43:53.000 --> 43:56.000
Will Pierre... Will your
husband be there?

43:56.000 --> 43:59.000
No, he's had to go away on business,
otherwise I'd send him to fetch you.

44:00.000 --> 44:03.000
Oh, I don't know.
No, I think I should stay at home.

44:03.000 --> 44:04.000
But that would be such a shame...

44:04.000 --> 44:07.000
to deprive Moscow of your charms
when you've only just arrived!

44:07.000 --> 44:11.089
Prince Andrei wouldn't want
you to shut yourself away, would he?

44:12.000 --> 44:14.000
No, perhaps not.

44:14.000 --> 44:16.000
- Oh, it's just a little family party!
- (THEY LAUGH)

44:16.000 --> 44:19.000
You will come, won't you?
Just to please me?

44:19.000 --> 44:20.000
Just for an hour?

44:20.000 --> 44:23.000
With your dear papa...
he's such delightful company!

44:23.000 --> 44:25.000
Oh, you won't refuse me, will you?

44:26.000 --> 44:27.000
No.

44:27.000 --> 44:29.000
Well, that's settled, then!

44:30.000 --> 44:32.000
A ce soir!

44:37.000 --> 44:39.000
(DOOR CLOSES)

44:49.000 --> 44:50.786
Countess Bezukhova, good

44:50.811 --> 44:53.024
- evening!
- You're very welcome.

44:57.000 --> 44:59.000
You came.

45:01.000 --> 45:03.000
"J'ai conçu pour mon
crime une juste terreur...

45:03.000 --> 45:08.000
J'ai pris la vie en haine,
et ma flamme en horreur.

45:09.000 --> 45:13.000
Je voulais en mourant
prendre soin de ma gloire,

45:13.000 --> 45:17.000
Et dérober au jour une flamme si noire :

45:17.000 --> 45:20.000
Je n'ai pu soutenir tes
larmes, tes combats...

45:20.000 --> 45:24.000
Je t'ai tout avoué...
je ne m'en repens pas,

45:24.000 --> 45:27.000
Pourvu que de ma mort
respectant les approches,

45:27.000 --> 45:30.000
Tu ne m'affliges plus
par d'injustes reproches,

45:30.000 --> 45:34.000
Et que tes vains secours
cessent de rappeler

45:34.000 --> 45:39.000
Un reste de chaleur tout prêt à s'exhaler."

45:41.000 --> 45:44.000
(APPLAUSE)

45:47.000 --> 45:50.000
There's dancing in the other room.
Come and dance with me.

45:50.000 --> 45:52.000
- No, I don't think I should.
- Just one dance.

45:52.000 --> 45:55.000
I think we really should be going.
My wife's not very well, you know?

45:55.000 --> 45:58.000
Oh, please don't deprive us
of your lovely daughter, Count.

45:58.000 --> 46:01.000
Come and sit with me and watch
the dancing for half an hour.

46:01.000 --> 46:03.000
Well...

46:04.000 --> 46:06.000
Half an hour?

46:06.000 --> 46:08.000
Very well, why not?

46:08.000 --> 46:09.000
Wonderful!

46:17.000 --> 46:20.560
I haven't been able to think
of a single thing except for you.

46:23.000 --> 46:25.000
I'm in love with you.

46:26.000 --> 46:30.573
- I've been in complete torment...
- Please! You mustn't say such things.

46:33.000 --> 46:36.000
I'm engaged... I'm in love with
someone else. What is that to me?

46:37.000 --> 46:40.614
Don't you understand,
I'm madly in love with you?

46:41.000 --> 46:43.000
You feel something, too. I know it.

46:46.000 --> 46:48.000
Don't leave me. Dance the next.

46:50.000 --> 46:52.000
(SHE GASPS)

46:52.000 --> 46:53.000
I can't!

47:05.000 --> 47:07.000
(SHE PANTS)

47:10.000 --> 47:13.000
You make such a lovely couple.

47:13.000 --> 47:15.000
I'm sorry you have to go so soon.

47:17.000 --> 47:19.000
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

47:19.000 --> 47:20.000
(SHE GASPS)

47:27.000 --> 47:28.554
Ana... Anatole!

47:59.000 --> 48:00.000
(SHE GASPS)

48:07.000 --> 48:08.000
No...

48:08.000 --> 48:11.262
- No, no, please...
- What can we do?

48:13.000 --> 48:16.429
I can't call on you openly.
Am I never to see you?

48:19.000 --> 48:22.793
I'll get word to you somehow.
We have to be together.

48:26.000 --> 48:28.000
No...

48:28.000 --> 48:29.000
No.

48:30.000 --> 48:32.000
Say yes.

48:32.000 --> 48:33.000
Give me your word!

48:33.000 --> 48:36.000
No, no!

48:36.000 --> 48:38.000
Ah! Well, there you are!

48:39.000 --> 48:42.000
I thought I'd lost you.
We really must go.

48:59.000 --> 49:00.622
If you please, miss...

49:03.000 --> 49:06.000
... a man asked me to give you this.

49:07.000 --> 49:11.000
- Thank you.
- You're welcome, miss.

49:14.000 --> 49:17.000
ANATOLE: 'Since last evening
my fate is sealed...

49:17.000 --> 49:19.000
'to be loved by you, or die.'

49:36.000 --> 49:39.000
So, she's the love of your life
and you want to elope with her?

49:39.000 --> 49:40.476
Are you going to tell her about

49:40.501 --> 49:42.000
- the Polish girl?
- Good God, no!

49:42.000 --> 49:45.000
Because you're still married
to that one, aren't you?

49:45.000 --> 49:48.000
- Who else knows about her?
- No-one. Just you...

49:49.000 --> 49:51.000
... and Pierre Bezukhov.

49:51.000 --> 49:53.000
Well. We'd better hope
the little Rostov girl

49:53.000 --> 49:56.000
- isn't going to confide in him, then.
- Why would she?

49:56.000 --> 49:58.000
Look here, Dolokhov,
are you going to help me or not?

50:09.000 --> 50:10.558
Did you read it?

50:11.000 --> 50:14.000
Yes, I couldn't help it.

50:14.000 --> 50:16.000
Sonya, he loves me!

50:17.000 --> 50:18.568
And I... I love him!

50:20.000 --> 50:24.000
- But what about Prince Andrei?
- Oh, that's... That's all over.

50:24.000 --> 50:26.000
- What? You're refusing him?
- I just told you, that's all over!

50:26.000 --> 50:29.000
I can't believe it. You've
loved him for a whole year,

50:29.000 --> 50:32.000
- and then, in three days...
- I know, I know...

50:32.000 --> 50:35.000
I know, but I feel as if
I've always loved Anatole.

50:35.000 --> 50:38.000
I know now that I've never
really loved anybody before,

50:38.000 --> 50:39.000
not even Andrei.

50:39.000 --> 50:41.000
I have no will when I'm with Anatole,

50:41.000 --> 50:44.000
it's like I'm his slave,
I'd do anything for him.

50:44.000 --> 50:45.000
Oh, God!

50:45.000 --> 50:47.558
Oh... what am I going to do?

50:48.000 --> 50:53.000
Well, I don't understand,
how could you let it go so far?

50:53.000 --> 50:56.000
Sonya, you don't know what it
feels like to be in love like this.

50:56.000 --> 50:59.000
I do know what it feels
like to be in love, Natasha.

50:59.000 --> 51:01.000
And SUFFER for it. But...

51:01.000 --> 51:04.000
this feels strange and wrong.

51:04.000 --> 51:06.000
What's stopping this man from
asking for your hand properly?

51:06.000 --> 51:09.000
If that's what he wants,
why can't he come to the house?

51:09.000 --> 51:12.000
Why doesn't he ask
your parents' consent?

51:12.000 --> 51:14.777
What if he just wants to... seduce you?

51:16.000 --> 51:18.000
How can you say that,
after you've read his letter?

51:18.000 --> 51:21.000
He loves me, Sonya!

51:21.000 --> 51:24.000
I'd do anything.
I'd... I'd run away with him!

51:24.000 --> 51:26.000
- But you'll ruin yourself!
- I don't care if I ruin myself,

51:26.000 --> 51:29.000
I WANT to ruin myself!

51:29.000 --> 51:30.784
The sooner the better.

51:32.000 --> 51:34.000
And this is... this is none
of your business!

51:34.000 --> 51:35.515
Just leave me alone! Just go!

51:37.000 --> 51:39.006
Well, I won't let it happen.

51:40.000 --> 51:41.000
I'll tell.

51:41.000 --> 51:42.000
Sonya!

51:43.000 --> 51:47.000
- If you do, you're my enemy forever!
- I'm not your enemy.

51:47.000 --> 51:49.000
Don't you see that
what you're doing is wrong?

51:49.000 --> 51:51.000
You don't understand anything!

51:52.000 --> 51:54.784
Oh, just go! Just... I hate you!

52:02.000 --> 52:03.000
(DOOR CLOSES)

52:03.000 --> 52:05.000
(PEN SCRATCHES)

52:08.000 --> 52:10.000
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

52:10.000 --> 52:13.000
If you please, miss,
there's a lady to see you.

52:17.000 --> 52:18.000
(SHE SIGHS)

52:22.000 --> 52:24.000
Princess Marya, I wasn't expecting...

52:24.000 --> 52:25.000
I have been in despair

52:25.000 --> 52:28.000
because of the misunderstanding
that happened between us.

52:28.000 --> 52:31.000
My brother loves you
and I will love you, too.

52:31.000 --> 52:34.000
I'm so sorry you weren't
properly received the other day.

52:34.000 --> 52:38.000
And Papa, too, he's not against you,
he's old and crotchety with us all.

52:38.000 --> 52:40.000
Can you forgive us?

52:41.000 --> 52:44.000
Of course. There's nothing to forgive.

52:45.000 --> 52:47.000
But...

52:48.000 --> 52:49.000
But...

52:50.000 --> 52:52.000
I have something to ask you.

52:54.000 --> 52:56.000
Will you tell Prince Andrei
when he comes

52:56.000 --> 53:00.000
that our engagement is at an end,
and I cannot be his wife?

53:02.000 --> 53:05.000
Oh, dear, we must have
offended you deeply...

53:05.000 --> 53:08.000
No, it's nothing to do
with that, it's... it's me.

53:09.000 --> 53:11.000
I'm the one who's at fault.

53:12.000 --> 53:14.000
I made a mistake.

53:14.000 --> 53:18.000
But tell him, please, that he is
released from the engagement,

53:18.000 --> 53:20.000
and ask his forgiveness.

53:20.000 --> 53:22.000
I'm sorry, that's all I can say.

54:00.000 --> 54:03.000
(NIGHT-TIME BUSTLE)

54:05.000 --> 54:07.000
Yah!

54:07.000 --> 54:08.000
Come on!

54:13.000 --> 54:16.000
(SHE GASPS)

54:16.000 --> 54:18.000
(HORSES WHINNY)

54:22.000 --> 54:25.000
Come with me, quickly.
She'll be out directly.

54:48.000 --> 54:51.000
You're to come with us,
sir, to the Countess.

54:51.000 --> 54:53.000
No, that's not right, she's to...

54:53.000 --> 54:55.000
- What do you mean? What Countess?
- You're to come with us, sir.

54:55.000 --> 54:58.000
(GRUNTING)

54:58.000 --> 54:59.000
(CLATTERING)

55:01.000 --> 55:02.000
Dolokhov!

55:02.000 --> 55:04.000
Let me through, damn you!

55:04.000 --> 55:06.000
We've been betrayed!

55:07.000 --> 55:08.000
(GATE CLATTERS)

55:14.000 --> 55:16.000
(SHE SOBS)

55:18.000 --> 55:21.000
(SHE CRIES OUT)

55:25.000 --> 55:27.000
Better that they should get away.

55:27.000 --> 55:31.000
It'll be a long time before he shows
his face in Moscow again, surely.

55:31.000 --> 55:34.000
Nevertheless, we have to face it, Ilya,

55:34.000 --> 55:35.000
she's ruined.

55:35.000 --> 55:37.000
But, my love,

55:37.000 --> 55:38.000
nothing happened.

55:38.000 --> 55:41.000
Her reputation is ruined...

55:41.000 --> 55:43.000
do you think it's possible
to keep a thing like this quiet?

55:43.000 --> 55:46.000
What will Prince Andrei
think when he hears about it?

55:46.000 --> 55:48.000
He'll throw her over and
then everyone will know why...

55:48.000 --> 55:50.000
- Poor, poor girl...
- "Poor girl"?

55:50.000 --> 55:52.000
SHE brought it upon herself!

55:53.000 --> 55:55.000
(BOTH SIGH)

55:55.000 --> 55:56.000
I think...

55:59.000 --> 56:01.000
I think I must challenge him, Natalya.

56:01.000 --> 56:03.000
And get yourself killed?

56:03.000 --> 56:06.000
Oh! How's that going to help?!

56:06.000 --> 56:08.000
(SHE SOBS AND SNIFFLES)

56:08.000 --> 56:11.000
Has she got anything
to say for herself?

56:12.000 --> 56:15.000
Nothing. Except she has
asked for Pierre Bezukhov.

56:15.000 --> 56:16.000
Oh!

56:16.000 --> 56:18.000
(SHE SOBS)

56:26.000 --> 56:28.000
Ah, Pierre! Such a silly situation...

56:28.000 --> 56:31.000
Wherever you are, there's depravity
and evil! You, come with me.

56:31.000 --> 56:33.000
Yes, yes, yes.

56:36.000 --> 56:39.000
What was your intention with
regard to the Countess Rostova?

56:39.000 --> 56:39.947
My dear fellow, you needn't

56:39.972 --> 56:41.000
- take that tone...
- Answer me!

56:41.000 --> 56:43.000
You couldn't marry her...
you're married already!

56:43.000 --> 56:46.000
- Was your plan to ruin her?I love her!
- You liar!

56:46.000 --> 56:49.000
Scoundrel! I'll smash your
head and spill your brains!

56:49.000 --> 56:51.000
Pierre, for God's sake!

56:51.000 --> 56:54.000
- Have you letters from her?
- One. One note.

56:54.000 --> 56:55.000
Hand it over.

56:55.000 --> 56:57.000
(HE PANTS)

57:00.000 --> 57:02.000
Now, you are never
to make contact with her again,

57:02.000 --> 57:05.000
never to SPEAK her name in society,

57:05.000 --> 57:09.622
and if I find you in Moscow after
midnight tonight, I WILL kill you.

57:11.000 --> 57:13.000
- Do you understand?
- Yes.

57:13.000 --> 57:14.000
(HE PANTS)

57:26.000 --> 57:27.000
(ORNAMENT CLUNKS)

57:27.000 --> 57:29.000
(RETREATING FOOTSTEPS)

57:35.000 --> 57:37.000
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

57:45.000 --> 57:47.878
- Have you seen him?
- Yes, I've seen him.

57:49.000 --> 57:50.000
What did he say?

57:51.000 --> 57:53.494
He's left Moscow.

57:58.000 --> 58:00.000
TEARFULLY: Was that your doing?

58:02.000 --> 58:05.000
I will go to him, wherever he is!

58:05.000 --> 58:07.000
I don't care what anybody thinks!

58:07.000 --> 58:10.000
Natasha, he could never be with
you honestly. He's a married man!

58:10.000 --> 58:12.000
He has a wife in Poland!

58:12.000 --> 58:13.715
No, I don't believe you!

58:16.000 --> 58:17.000
It's true.

58:21.000 --> 58:23.000
(SHE SNIFFLES)

58:25.000 --> 58:27.000
(SHE SOBS)

58:27.000 --> 58:28.000
No...

58:30.000 --> 58:32.000
(SHE CRIES)

58:38.000 --> 58:39.000
No...

58:39.000 --> 58:40.801
Pierre...

58:42.000 --> 58:43.000
Please, no...

58:43.000 --> 58:45.000
All right.

58:48.000 --> 58:50.000
All right.

58:52.000 --> 58:54.000
(SHE SOBS BITTERLY)

58:56.000 --> 58:58.000
It's all right.

58:58.000 --> 59:00.000
(SHE WEEPS)

59:00.000 --> 59:02.000
It's all right.

59:02.000 --> 59:03.000
Shh...

59:05.000 --> 59:08.000
ANDREI: 'My dearest Natasha...

59:08.000 --> 59:11.000
'I have been thinking of you
constantly these past few months,

59:11.000 --> 59:15.137
'and now I am recovering, our
separation will at last be over.

59:16.000 --> 59:19.000
'I shall come to you as
soon as I arrive in Moscow.'

